casebody.data:
Lisa Ann WILDER, an Individual, Appellant,
v.
Kurt S. MASON, Respondent. No. 76078 Supreme Court of Nevada. FILED NOVEMBER 19, 2018

Ladah Law Firm

Law Offices of Karl H. Smith/Las Vegas

ORDER DISMISSING APPEAL

We previously entered an order directing appellant to show cause why this appeal should not be dismissed for lack of jurisdiction because it appeared that the district court had not yet entered an appealable order. See NRAP 3A(b). Appellant has now filed a notice of withdrawal of appeal. We treat the notice as a motion to voluntarily dismiss this appeal and, cause appearing, grant the motion. This appeal is dismissed. NRAP 42(b).

It is so ORDERED.
